<sec id="eva12803-sec-0012" class="sec">
 <span class="label" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">3.3</span>
 <div class="title" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Phenotypic evolution in response to drought</div>
 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">We found significant evolutionary change in several traits and in trait variances. These evolutionary changes were shown by differences between ancestors and descendants grown under common conditions. Regarding phenology, days to emergence differed significantly by generation; mean day of emergence was 4.4 days earlier for the drought generation than the pre‐drought generation (Table 
  <a rid="eva12803-tbl-0002" ref-type="table" href="#eva12803-tbl-0002">2</a>). Emergence time significantly decreased with elevation, but the interaction between elevation and generation was not significant. The mean seed mass covariate was significant (Table 
  <a rid="eva12803-tbl-0002" ref-type="table" href="#eva12803-tbl-0002">2</a>).
 </p>
